---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Uzbekistan Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/uzbekistan/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Kazakhstan for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/kazakhstan' },
  { title: 'Georgia for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/georgia' },
  { title: 'Turkey for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/turkey' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'uzbekistanFit', header: 'Uzbekistan Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'UZS$6.3M-9M/mo', uzbekistanFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'UZS$7.4M-10.5M/mo', uzbekistanFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'UZS$5.7M-8.1M/mo', uzbekistanFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'UZS$5.3M-7.5M/mo', uzbekistanFit: 'Very Good' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'UZS$5.7M-9M', annual: 'UZS$68.4M-108M' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'UZS$7.8M-12M', annual: 'UZS$93.6M-144M' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'UZS$10.5M-16.1M', annual: 'UZS$126M-193.2M' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Visit', monthly: 'UZS$300K-800K/visit', annual: 'Very affordable' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'UZS$2M-5M/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Uzbekistan 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors in Uzbekistan. Silk Road cities, Samarkand beauty, affordable living, and coverage for visitors 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Uzbekistan"
  subheadline="Uzbekistan offers stunning Silk Road cities, Samarkand's turquoise domes, ancient history, and very affordable living—Central Asia's cultural jewel opening to tourism."
  heroImage="/images/countries/uzbekistan-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Uzbekistan</h2>
  <p>
    Uzbekistan offers stunning Silk Road architecture, Samarkand's famous turquoise domes, Bukhara's ancient medressas, and Khiva's preserved old city. For history-loving retirees seeking ancient wonders at very low cost, Uzbekistan provides extraordinary cultural heritage.
  </p>

  <p>
    Tashkent is the capital with best healthcare. Samarkand has iconic monuments. Bukhara offers preserved medieval city. Khiva is complete walled city. Most extended visitors base in Tashkent for healthcare; explore historic cities for experiences.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Limited; Turkey/Dubai evacuation common</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Uzbek; Russian widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> UZS$10M-20M/month (~$800-1,600 USD); very affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Continental; hot summers; cold winters</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Silk Road; hospitable; opening</li>
      <li><strong>Visa:</strong> Visa-free for many nationalities</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Uzbekistan Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Uzbekistan healthcare is limited—Tashkent has some private clinics but specialists are limited. Public system underfunded. Complex cases require evacuation to Istanbul (4-hour flight) or Dubai. Healthcare improving but still basic by Western standards.
  </p>

  <p>
    Private healthcare in Tashkent is very affordable but limited. Historic cities have basic healthcare only. International insurance with strong evacuation coverage essential.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">International Evacuation Essential</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Uzbekistan cannot treat most complex conditions. Istanbul and Dubai provide backup (4-hour flights). Include Turkey/UAE in insurance coverage. Don't rely on local healthcare for serious conditions. Evacuation coverage is non-negotiable.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Uzbekistan has accessible visa policies (reformed in 2018):
  </p>

  <h3>Visa-Free Entry</h3>
  <p>
    30-day visa-free for many nationalities including US, EU, UK. Major reform in 2018.
  </p>

  <h3>E-Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For nationalities not covered by visa-free. Simple online process.
  </p>

  <h3>Extended Stay</h3>
  <p>
    Registration required for stays over 3 days. Extensions available.
  </p>

  <h3>Residence</h3>
  <p>
    Limited options for foreigners. Work or business visas possible.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Uzbekistan:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> Travel insurance strongly recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Extended stay:</strong> International coverage essential</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Turkey/UAE coverage critical</li>
    <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Consider extremes—hot summers, cold winters</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Uzbekistan</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance with Turkey/Dubai evacuation coverage essential. Tashkent has limited private options. Historic cities have basic care only. Don't economize on evacuation—healthcare limitations are real.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Uzbekistan, evacuation coverage critical:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Uzbekistan</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong regional network, Turkey access</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>Istanbul access:</strong> Regional medical hub</li>
    <li><strong>Don't economize:</strong> Evacuation is essential</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage with strong evacuation.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Uzbekistan (UZS ~12,500 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Tashkent base:</strong> Best local options</li>
    <li><strong>Don't cut evacuation:</strong> This is essential</li>
    <li><strong>Turkey network:</strong> Use for complex care</li>
    <li><strong>Affordable living:</strong> Very low daily costs</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Silk Road Enthusiast, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,000/month pension. Extended tourism. Tashkent base.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with Turkey/UAE evacuation.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~UZS$6.5M/month (~$520). Historic exploration; comprehensive backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Russian-Speaker, 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €1,800/month pension. Extended stay. Samarkand focused.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with strong evacuation.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~UZS$8M/month (~$640). Language ease; global coverage.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Budget History Lover, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $1,500/month income. Tourism rotation. Mobile.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with essential evacuation.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~UZS$5.7M/month (~$455). Budget stretch; essential coverage.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Uzbekistan safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very safe—low crime. Authoritarian government but stable. Tourist areas well-managed. Police presence visible. No terrorism issues. Safe for walking. One of safest destinations in region. Normal precautions apply.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need Russian?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Helpful—Russian widely spoken. Uzbek is official but Russian remains common. English limited outside tourism. Healthcare often in Russian. Learning Russian basics very helpful. Younger generation may speak some English.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's Samarkand like?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Stunning—Registan Square is one of world's most beautiful. Turquoise domes, intricate tilework, ancient history. Timur's legacy. UNESCO World Heritage. Peak of Silk Road architecture. Unforgettable for history lovers.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about the climate?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Extreme continental—very hot summers (40°C+), cold winters (-10 to -20°C). Spring (April-May) and autumn (Sep-Oct) best times. Low humidity. Clear skies. Air conditioning essential summer. Not tropical—genuine seasons.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Uzbekistan coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Uzbekistan authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
